==English==
===Noun===
'''[[mother-in-law]] [[style]]'''
# [[linguistic|Linguistic]] or [[anthropological]] term for the style of speech and manners which are to be observed between an Australian aboriginal man and his [[mother-in-law]] (ie. wife's mother).  Depending on the particular people this can go so as far as an entirely separate [[vocubulary]] of words.  (Reference: ''Macquarie Aboriginal Words'', [[w:Macquarie University|Macquarie University]], 1994, paperback ISBN 0-949757-79-9, introduction.)
